;{{nihongo|{{va|Mei Misaki}}|見崎 鳴|Misaki Mei}}
:{{voiced by|[[Natsumi Takamori]]<ref name="ann jp cast"/>|[[Monica Rial]]<ref name="ann eng cast"/>}}
:Played by: [[Ai Hashimoto]]<ref name="live cast" /> (live-action film)
:An unusual girl who wears a white [[eyepatch]] over her left eye,{{gnr|ch|1}} Kōichi first meets her on the elevator of Yūmigaoka Hospital, as she is going to deliver a doll to her "poor other half" in the second basement (it comes out in bits that her other half is deceased, her cousin, and later is revealed to be her twin sister in episode 0).{{gnr|ch|1}} At school, she is completely ignored by her classmates. When Kōichi goes out of his way to try to interact with her, she warns him not to, but relents and gradually opens up to him about her situation after Kōichi is also ignored by the class.{{gnr|ch|8}} She reveals to Kōichi that her left eye is a [[Ocular prosthesis|doll's eye]], and that she has a special ability,{{gnr|ch|3}} noting later in the story that she is able to see the "color of death", that is, identify people who are dead and those close to death.{{gnr|ch|17}}

===Kōichi's relatives===
;{{nihongo|{{va|Yōsuke Sakakibara}}|榊原 陽介|Sakakibara Yōsuke}}
:{{voiced by|[[Takurō Kitagawa]]|[[Christopher Ayres]]}}
:Kōichi's father is a college professor who is doing [[work abroad|research in India]]. He regularly calls his son to chat, but does not give much detail about their family background, opting instead to complain about the heat.<ref>{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|p=17,37}}</ref> The phone connection typically becomes filled with static and drops just as Yōsuke might say something informative.

;{{nihongo|{{va|Ritsuko Sakakibara}}|榊原 理津子|Sakakibara Ritsuko}}
:Kōichi's mother, she died 15 years ago right after giving birth to him. She was a student in Yomiyama Middle School's Class 3-3 back in 1972, and was thus one of Misaki Yomiyama's classmates.{{gnr|ch|1}} It is later revealed that she died while Reiko was in Class 3-3; and was therefore a victim of the curse that year. Her maiden name was {{nihongo|Ritsuko Mikami|三神 理津子|Mikami Ritsuko}}.<ref name="book p648">{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|p=648}} "十五年前に死んだ母、榊原理津子(旧姓、三神)。その十一歳年下の妹、すなわちぼくの実の
<ruby><rb>叔母</rb><rp>(</rp><rt>おば</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby>である三神怜子――怜子さんが、これから転入する学校の教師で、しかもクラスの副担任であるという偶然はある意味、大いに心強い話ではあった。"</ref>

;{{nihongo|{{va|Reiko Mikami}}|三神 怜子|Mikami Reiko}}<ref name="book p648"/>
:{{voiced by|Naoko Sakakibara (Reiko),<ref name="ann jp cast"/> Misayo Miyamaki (Ms. Mikami)<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150411000834/http://www.another-anime.jp/character/images/chara-box-11.jpg|url=http://www.another-anime.jp/character/images/chara-box-11.jpg|script-title=ja:三神先生|trans-title=Ms. Mikami|publisher=[[P.A.Works]]|archivedate=April 11, 2015|accessdate=August 11, 2015|language=Japanese}}</ref>{{efn|The voice actor "Misayo Miyamaki" was a pseudonym, with the name being an anagram for Misaki Yomiyama}}|Molly Searcy<ref name="ann eng cast"/>}}
:Played by: [[Ai Kato]] (live-action film)
:Kōichi's aunt and Ritsuko's younger sister.<ref name="book p648"/> She has been hanging out with Kōichi at the grandparents home while Kōichi's dad has been away. At the beginning of the story, she gives him advice about Yomiyama Middle School through a series of "rules".{{gnr|ch|1}} She usually returns home exhausted after work.{{gnr|ch|4|,6}} She was in class 3-3 15 years ago when Kōichi's mother died.{{gnr|ch|6}} It is later revealed that she and Koichi's current teacher are the same person. Chibiki tells Mei and Kouichi that Ms. Mikami was the Class 3-3 homeroom teacher in 1996, the last year the calamity happened, and that making her assistant homeroom teacher this year put a burden on her. In the anime, it is revealed that Ms. Mikami was the extra person.

===Mei's relatives===
;{{nihongo|{{va|Kirika|Yukiyo Misaki}}|霧果}}
:{{voiced by|[[Hitomi Harada]]|[[Tiffany Grant]]}} 
:She is an artist and the owner of "Blue Eyes Empty to All, In the Twilight of Yomi", a [[ball-jointed doll]] store and museum.{{gnr|ch|3}} Kōichi later confirms she is Mei Misaki's adoptive mother,{{gnr|ch|8}} but they have a somewhat distant relationship where they talk to each other like strangers.{{gnr|ch|9}} Mei reveals that her mother had a stillbirth 12 years ago, which made her obsessed with dolls; this hobby has led to her and Mei treating each other as strangers.{{gnr|ch|17}} Her real name is {{nihongo|Yukiyo Misaki|見崎 ユキヨ|Misaki Yukiyo}}.{{gnr|ch|17}}

;{{nihongo|{{va|Misaki Fujioka}}|藤岡 未咲|Fujioka Misaki}}
:{{voiced by|[[Hiromi Igarashi]]}}
:First introduced as Mei's "other half"{{gnr|ch|1}} and later as her cousin,{{gnr|ch|3}} she was the person whom Mei was delivering a present to at the basement of Yūmigaoka Hospital,{{gnr|ch|1}} where Kōichi learns houses the memorial chapel.{{gnr|ch|2}} In reality, she is Mei's twin sister, raised separately after birth, though they occasionally met each other.  Has a more cheerful personality than Mei. Misaki and Mei's biological mother is named Mitsuyo.{{gnr|ch|17}} Misaki died in the hospital from [[leukemia]] in April.<ref>{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|pp=584–593}}</ref>

;{{nihongo|{{va|Amane}}|天根|Amane}}
:{{voiced by|[[Sayuri Sadaoka]]|Vicki Barosh}}
:The receptionist at the doll shop and museum.{{gnr|ch|3}} Whenever she sees Kōichi, she offers him a student-discounted admission to their museum.{{gnr|ch|3|,|5}} Mei later reveals that she is her grand-aunt.{{gnr|ch|8}}

===Yomiyama North Middle School===

====Class 3-3 students====
;{{nihongo|{{va|Tomohiko Kazami}}|風見 智彦|Kazami Tomohiko}}
:{{voiced by|[[Mitsuhiro Ichiki]]|[[Josh Grelle]]<ref name="ann eng cast"/>}}, Takashi Waka (live-action film)
:He's one of the class delegates and a [[meganekko|glasses-wearing]] honor student.{{gnr|ch|1}} He and Teshigawara are childhood friends.{{gnr|ch|1}}

;{{nihongo|{{va|Yukari Sakuragi}}|桜木 ゆかり|Sakuragi Yukari}}
:{{voiced by|[[Ai Nonaka]]<ref name="ann jp cast"/>|[[Brittney Karbowski]]<ref name="ann eng cast"/>}}, Maya Okano (live-action film)
:The class 3-3 representative for the girls side.{{gnr|ch|1|,|5}} Her appearance is friendly. In May, when she learns that her mother died in a car accident, she ends up falling down the stairs and impaling her neck on the sharp end of her [[umbrella]].<ref name="book p185">{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|p=185}}</ref>{{gnr|ch|4}}

;{{nihongo|{{va|Naoya Teshigawara}}|敕使河原直哉|Teshigawara Naoya}}
:{{voiced by|[[Tomoaki Maeno]]<ref name="ann jp cast"/>|[[Chris Patton]]<ref name="ann eng cast"/>}}, Kiyotaka Uji (live-action film)
:A classmate who befriends Kōichi, whom he nicknames "Sakaki".{{gnr|ch|1}} His appearance is a little taller than other boys and cheery. A sports lover with a superficial personality, he was asked to explain the situation to Kōichi but has trouble going through with it.{{gnr|vol|1}}

;{{nihongo|{{va|Yūya Mochizuki}}|望月 優矢|Mochizuki Yūya}}
:{{voiced by|[[Kazutomi Yamamoto]]<ref name="ann jp cast"/>|[[Clint Bickham]]}}, Kai Inowaki (live-action film)
:A schoolmate and member of the Art Club.{{gnr|ch|3}} He along with Teshigawara help Kōichi unravel the 3-3 calamity. Kōichi thinks he has a crush on Ms. Mikami the assistant homeroom teacher as he often inquires as to her health and whereabouts.{{gnr|ch|3}}

;{{nihongo|{{va|Izumi Akazawa}}|赤沢 泉美|Akazawa Izumi}}
:{{voiced by|[[Madoka Yonezawa]]<ref name="ann jp cast"/>|[[Jessica Boone]]<ref name="ann eng cast"/>}}, Mika Akizuki (live-action film)
:A student in charge of countermeasures, she devises and upholds means to deal with the calamity of Class 3-3.{{gnr|ch|3|,|6|,|7}} She replaces her friend Yukari as the class representative on the girls side in June.{{gnr|ch|7}} She resents Mei and Kōichi for breaking the class rule of not interacting with the person who is "not there", feeling that their actions have undermined the countermeasures and have caused the deaths to continue.{{gnr|ch|6|,|11}}<ref>{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|pages=434, 562–569}}</ref> In the novel, during the summer trip, she is pursued by Mineko Numata, and dies from falling off a veranda and [[cervical fracture|breaking her neck]].<!-- Don't remove it because of spoilers or differences with the anime. This describes the events in the novel. --><ref name="book p660">{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|p=660}}</ref> In the manga and anime, her hair is styled in [[bunches]]. In the afterword of the manga series, Ayatsuji wrote that Akazawa was a supporting character in the novels, but that manga artist Kiyohara give her a bigger role, which worked well for the climax and the big twist in the adaptation.{{gnr|vol|Omnibus|:afterword}}

;{{nihongo|{{va|Ikuo Takabayashi}}|高林郁夫|Takabayashi Ikuo}}
:{{voiced by|Shou Takano|[[Blake Shepard]]<ref name="ann eng cast"/>}}
:A classmate who is noted to occasionally miss school because of his weak heart condition. His appearance is thin and a bit smaller than other boys. He is usually seen sitting at the sidelines during [[physical education|P.E.]].{{volume needed|date=August 2015}} In June, he suffers a fatal heart attack.<ref>{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|p=267}}</ref>{{gnr|ch|7}}
<!--- NEED NOTABILITY
;{{nihongo|{{va|Takako Sugiura}}|杉浦多佳子|Sugiura Takako}}{{importance-inline|date=August 2015|reason=episodic death?}}
:{{voiced by|[[Misato Fukuen]]|[[Emily Neves]]}}
:She is always in Akazawa's group. She died during the summer trip, one of the seven "Deaths of August".<ref name="book p660"/>

;{{nihongo|{{va|Yumi Ogura}}|小椋 由美|Ogura Yumi}}{{importance-inline|date=August 2015|reason=episodic death?}}
:{{voiced by|[[Iori Nomizu]]|[[Tiffany Grant]]}}
:She is the sister of [[hikikomori]] (social recluse) Atsushi Ogura, who dies after a truck carrying an [[excavator]] crashes into his house. Atsushi is one of the "Deaths of July".<ref>{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|p=517}} "七月三十日、午後五時二十分。(…)大型工事用車両が(…)家に突っ込んで(…)敦志は(…)重傷を全身に負う結果となり、三十一日未明(…)息を引き取った。"</ref><ref>{{Harvnb|Ayatsuji|2009|p=518}} "三人めの＜七月の死者＞。"</ref>

;{{nihongo|{{va|Junta Nakao}}|中尾 順太|Nakao Junta}}{{importance-inline|date=August 2015|reason=episodic death?}}
:{{voiced by|Kengo Kasai|Houston Hayes}}
:He appears to have a crush on Akazawa, which is what drives his decision to participate in the summer trip, during which he died, making him one of the seven "Deaths of August".<ref name="book p660"/>

;{{nihongo|{{va|Manabu Maejima}}|前島 学|Maejima Manabu}}{{importance-inline|date=August 2015|reason=episodic death?}}
:{{voiced by|Keisuke Koumoto}}
:A member of the [[kendo]] club. He died during the summer trip when he was stabbed by Takabayashi's grandmother from the back, he's one of the seven "Deaths of August".<ref name="book p660"/>

;{{nihongo|{{va|Shigeki Yonemura}}|米村 茂樹|Yonemura Shigeki}}{{importance-inline|date=August 2015|reason=episodic death?}}
:He is a ranked A student in class. He died during the summer trip, one of the seven "Deaths of August".<ref name="book p660"/>
